name: Larry Underwood
tweet: ChatGPT is, in fact, brilliant in many ways but it doesn't take much to get it to completely invent things which it is utterly certain are correct despite being 100% wrong. And every time it apologies for getting something wrong, it corrects itself with more made up nonsense.

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I told ChatGPT that it was absolutely wrong. Thankfully, it apologised and told me the correct lyrics:  "The Little Bombardier His trousers were tight And his belt was too And he carried his weight In a long thin zoo"  And so on ...

name: Klay Thompson
tweet: @elonmusk @ggreenwald Not even the AI bots can escape the culture war - Bing vs ChatGPT.

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I told ChatGPT that I had some doubt about those lyrics. Its response?   "I can assure you that those are the correct lyrics to "The Little Bombardier" by David Bowie."

name: Kevin Allman
tweet: Hello ChatGPT, please write my book

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I told ChatGPT that those lyrics were made up and didn't exist. It apologised again and told me its 'corrected' version:   "Hey little bombardier A purveyor of cannon fire Little bombardier But no one wants to hire Little bombardier There's a place in your world." etc ...

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: Helpfully, ChatGPT tells me that "the lyrics describe the Little Bombardier as "mangled and tangled," with "twisted limbs and a broken body." Again, these seem to be completely invented lyrics. I can't find them anywhere, at least.

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I then asked ChatGPT about The Little Bombardier. ChatGPT told me he became a beggar.  I asked for its evidence for that and it told me that, again, it was mistaken. He had not become a beggar but his wartime injuries had made him an outcast.

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: That lyric appears to be 100% made up. And it certainly doesn't mention Halloween Jack. After a little argument. ChatGPT eventually told me that there are no songs mentioning Halloween Jack. I said that this is wrong. There is a song. Luckily, ChatGPT found it ...

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I also asked ChatGPT which songs mention Halloween Jack. Here's one of the responses: In "Sweet Thing," Bowie sings "Who's that down at the end of the alley? / He's looking kind of scary / He's brandishing an iron chain / That he's a psychopath, a killer."

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: Here's another one ChatGPT says is about Ziggy: "Starry Eyes" by The Records - This 1979 power pop hit includes the lyrics, "I could have been someone / Well so could anyone / You took my dreams from me when I first found you."

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: I asked ChatGPT who had sung about Ziggy Stardust. Here's one it told me about: "Ziggy" by Celine Dion - This 1996 song by Celine Dion, which was co-written by Bowie, includes the lyrics "Ziggy played guitar, jamming good with Weird and Gilly / And the spiders from Mars."

name: Larry Underwood
tweet: ChatGPT is insane. It just makes stuff up. I understand how it works but the results were still ridiculous. Every time I pointed out it was mistaken it apologised and then made something else up.
